centuriatus: the centurions, sixty in each legion, were appointed by the consul through the military tribunes, on grounds of merit, virtutis causa.

veneant atque venierint: the Latin inverts our English order, partly here for euphony, but cf. Verr. 4, 132 iniurias nullas Graeci gravius ferunt ac tulerunt.

12 quid: sc. possumus putare: though the sense of putare is changed.
